                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/symfony/edit/master/knpu/extra-form-theming/form-options-variables.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>We now know that these form variables kick butt, <em>and</em> we know how to override them
from inside a template. But, could we <em>also</em> control these from inside of our form
class?</p>
<p>Earlier, I mentioned that the <em>options</em> for a field are totally different than the
<em>variables</em> for a field. Occasionally, a field has an option - like <code>placeholder</code> -
<em>and</em> a variable with the same name, but that's not always true. But clearly, there
must be <em>some</em> connection between options and variables. So what is it?!</p>
<h2 id="form-type-classes-amp-options">Form Type Classes &amp; Options <a class="headerlink" href="form-options-variables#form-type-classes-amp-options" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>First, behind every field type is a class. Obviously, for the <code>subFamily</code> field,
the class behind this is <code>EntityType</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="1e23498bb7">
