</p>
<p><code>name</code> is a <em>text</em> type, so the class behind it, is, well, <code>TextType</code>. I'll use
the <code>Shift</code>+<code>Shift</code> shortcut in my editor to open the <code>TextType</code> file, from the
Symfony Form component:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="0664602efb">
