<p>Apparently the <code>TextType</code> has a <code>compound</code> option, and it defaults to <code>false</code>.</p>
<h2 id="form-type-inheritance">Form Type Inheritance <a class="headerlink" href="form-options-variables#form-type-inheritance" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Earlier, when we talked about form theme blocks, I mentioned that the field types
have a built-in <em>inheritance</em> system. Well, technically, <code>TextType</code> extends <code>AbstractType</code>,
but behind-the-scenes, the <code>TextType</code>'s parent type is <code>FormType</code>. In fact, <em>every</em>
field ultimately inherits options from <code>FormType</code>. Open that class:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="cf5f4414ec">
