</p>
<div class="admonition tip"><p class="admonition-title"><span class="fa fa-lightbulb-o"></span> Tip</p><p>Wondering how you would know what the "parent" type of a field is? Each <code>*Type</code> class
has a <code>getParent()</code> method that will tell you. If you don't see one, then it's
defaulting to <code>FormType</code>.</p>
</div><p>This is cool because it <em>also</em> has a <code>configureOptions()</code> method that adds a <em>bunch</em>
of options:</p>
