</p>
<p>Symfony gives us a <code>label</code> <em>option</em> as a convenient way to ultimately set the <code>label</code>
variable.</p>
<p>Close up all those classes. Here's a question: we know how to set the <code>help</code> variable
from inside of a Twig template. But could we somehow set this variable from inside
of the <code>GenusFormType</code> class? Yes, and there are actually <em>two</em> cool ways to do it.
Let's check them out.</p>

    
